Northern Ireland Police Say Man Charged With Terrorism Offences

-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 
2011-08-04T07:04:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/northern-ireland-police-say-man-charged-with-terrorism-offences.html
Northern Ireland police charged a 68-
year old man with terrorist offences including possession of
firearms with intent to endanger life and an offence under the
explosive substances act.  The man, arrested in west  Belfast  yesterday, is also
charged with having items for terrorist purposes, a police
spokesman said in a recorded message late yesterday. The arrest
was made by police investigating dissident republican terrorist
activity, according to the spokesman. The man will appear in
court in Belfast today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Colm Heatley in Belfast at 
 cheatley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge in  London  at 
 Ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 